The engagements were still ongoing by Sunday evening and were likely to go on into the late night. JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa's longer address to the nation on Sunday on the outcomes of the meetings he had today with various business, religious and government leaders on the way forward for South Africa on the coronavirus. The engagements were still ongoing by Sunday evening and were likely to go on into the late night. Minister in the Presidency, Jackson Mthembu, said it would not be fair to address the nation late in the night should the meeting conclude late on Sunday. An update will be provided on Monday, 23 March. Minister Mthembu updates the media on the Command Council meeting https://t.co/3aamPvYjpI 